result.execSummary:
The defendant Mark David Culbreath was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Mark David Culbreath is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Mark David Culbreath was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Mark David Culbreath was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: Defendant Mark David Culbreath in court.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.
Defense counsel called the court requesting to have the defendant's probation review hearing during the morning session.

Defendant Mark David Culbreath in court with attorney Christopher J. Cherella.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 3:    Defendant sentenced to serve  9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, to run concurrent as to each count, with credit for 3 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply for work. 

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS with the following conditions as to probation are as follows:
*  Pay costs, all surcharges, assessments, and supervision fees out of bail on deposit, if any, or during the period of probation.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  Obtain and maintain employment.
*  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY
*  AODA assessment with follow up care and treatment. 
*  Attend and successfully complete Batterers Intervention Program (BIP)
*  Attend Anger Management Classes.
*  Attend treatment and counseling programs a determined by the agent.
*  No violent contact with the victim which rises to the level of a probable cause for arrest for "domestic abuse harrassment"
*  No possession of any firearms or weapons.
*  Complete the "Wiser Choice" program.

CONDITION OF PROBATION:  COURT SENTENCED Defendant to serve 30 days condition time at the House of Correction (HOC). Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the Condition time sentenced and scheduled this case for a Probation Review Hearing on 12-11-2015 at 01:30 pm in Branch 38.  

Received and filed with court:
*  Memorandum of Conditions of Probation
*  Several letters / correspondence
*  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief Form
Received and Filed, five letters on behalf of the defendant and five attendant reports from Wiser Choice along with a cover letter.
Order to Produce for Pre-Trial Conference on August 17, 2015 @ 8:15am Received and Filed
Sentencing hearing scheduled for 08-11-2015 at 01:30 pm.

Statements to the Court by the victim regarding the No Contact Order.  Arguments to the Court by defense counsel.
Court will take under advisement, but declines to modify No Contact Order at this time.

Defendant Mark David Culbreath in court with attorney Christopher J. Cherella.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

As to Count 1 and Count 3:
Defendant waives constitutional rights, enters a plea of GUILTY  and is examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum  received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the Complaint as a factual basis for judgment.  Court finds defendant guilty as charged in the Amended Information/Complaint and enters a judgment of conviction.

As to Count 2:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders Count 2   DISMISSED.

Court orders case adjourned for sentencing hearing in Branch 4.  Parties are advised that EFFECTIVE August 3, 2015, this case will be assigned to JUDGE WAGNER, BRANCH 38, in Room 504 in the Courthouse.
No PSI ordered.
